{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Cloud*. Using *JIRA Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRASERVER-66387].
  {panel}

As a project admin would be nice to be able to have more advanced editing capabilities with workflows related to the project.

With project workflows, would be nice to be able to:
 * edit workflows;
 * edit a transition's properties;
 * edit a transition's conditions;
 * edit any validators;
 * edit any post-functions;

h3. Summary
When using the [Jira Cloud for Slack (Official)|https://marketplace.atlassian.com/plugins/com.atlassian.jira.slack/cloud/overview] integration. If you leave a comment on a JIRA issue using the \{noformat} directive, a notification will be displayed in Slack that ignores those directives and will interpret the text inside (like bullets and numbered lists) using JIRA markup formatting rules.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
* Associate a JIRA project with a Slack room
* Leave a comment in a JIRA issue using the following notation: 

{code}
{noformat}
* testing bullets
{noformat}
{code}
{code}
{noformat}
# testing numbered list
{noformat}
{code}

 !testing bullets and numbered list - JIRA Side.png|thumbnail! 

h3. Expected Results
The notification displayed in the Slack channel should follow the same formatting rules that were used in the comment made in JIRA. 

h3. Actual Results
The notification displayed in Slack will ignore the \{noformat} directive, interpreting the text inside using JIRA markup formatting rules. 

 !results in Slack.png|thumbnail!

{quote}
Currently, if the user would like to change the condition of multiple transition attributes (like the condition, for example), they would have to do it one-by-one in every transition, in every workflow.

This could cause some inconvenience for the users, especially when there are a lot of transitions and workflows that require such changes. It would be more efficient if we could perform bulk changes of these transition attributes.
{quote}

I can understand this has been raised before and was closed as *won't do*: [JRACLOUD\-32445: Allow bulk change of workflow transition attribute (condition, validator, or post\-function)|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-32445] However, there is some case where it is inevitable where there are large numbers of things in every direction.

Hope you can re-consider this.
